unting and Transparency','Challenges','Tracking the funds that flow into and through your group is essential for ensuring that money gets where it\'s supposed to go and that your group stays within legal compliance. Transparent accounting allows people within your group to confidently answer questions about how money is being allocated and spent, which can quell the hurt feelings and suspicion that arise when stakeholders feel like they\'re being left in the dark.','recwIrBHEx2GzqFM3, recWL774hB9n2FtTm, recNKcrxQjV2NUa49, recqlRPlAaB0H3miD','','','','',''),(12,'reccBNxz18IZGnMaN','Accounting Templates','Tutorials','The following is a spreadsheet template created for Occupy Sandy to keep track of its income and expenditures:\n\nIncome and Expenditures Workbook Template\nThe last sheet is a \"Public Summary\" that pulls content from other sheets in the workbook. This sheet was embedded and published on the OccupySandy.net WordPress website for transparency.\nIf using this template, you might consider locking equations cells in order to prevent accidental overwriting.','recqlRPlAaB0H3miD, recWL774hB9n2FtTm, recNmMk2QPPkX908b','recMF0w6LFawMmuLx','recIHs2E4fd0jfGHk','','',''),(13,'reczohhg7MUhNOqLA','Acquiring and Sharing Vehicles','Challenges','Getting things around a relief area requires regular access to vehicles. While rentals can work in the short-run, if you plan to maintain relief and recovery efforts for a longer period, it will prove far more cost effective for the network to use vehicles it actually ownsâ€”whether those are acquired via donation or purchase. Managing, coordinating and sharing community vehicles can be challenging for a relief effort.','recnebUtIIFB2MmCh, recoo0FF7LYlbK8Ge, recBIZuY8a6ia14Sr, recHWrkHpcBDNu2Ll','','','','',''),(14,'recAjbbrfwRgp5a3f','active collaboration','glossary','','','recM2XJddaSgIBuKp','','','',''),(15,'recuCWMN0JHkrFQSd','Active Learning Network for Accountability','Toolboxes','','reclppEYWUzwZuiuA','','','','',''),(16,'rec6ZlhWyLRDsGbuT','Adding Feeds to FeedWordPress','Tutorials','Go to Syndication >> add Multiple.\nPaste RSS feeds - one per line - and click Add\nCreate a list of automatically unchecked feeds.  Those have errors and you\'ll need to resubmit them.  Press \"Add\".\nWe also recommend you add author information to individual feeds so they sort using WordPress\'s built in Author functionality.\n\n\n\nYou can add information about authors of feed posts by editting their user infoirmation.  I like to add the feed\'s \"about\" information as the user\'s \"about info\".\n\nUsers > All Users\nFill out the relevant profile info and click \"Save\".\n\n\nCheck all the feed titles.  Are they conveying the right information?  If not, change their titles.','recQZtGMy5sgFvIRi','recbgLoJeve3wuH6N, recn2Fe6mUozKtlNU','','','',''),(17,'recDgw66lSOLoNMab','Advocates and activists using data to push for change','Workflows','','recWNX91VUaintM4q, rec1C1xZ9gNa3wVb7','','','','Willow',''),(18,'recigrIquSasBAUnY','Affordable and Clean Energy','SDG','','','recqPkDhp14BArq8P, receqqigIUe2Hm5lw, recDbviEVwaAoN5or','','','',''),(19,'receKP4AFVpyJoQvd','affordable/reliable/ sustainable/modem energy for all','glossary','','','receqqigIUe2Hm5lw','','','',''),(20,'recjhdgX6nG1tEWrP','Agency Liason','Use Case','Meet the needs of your constituents in an ethical framework you agree with by working with (or avoiding) response agencies in the area through talking and working with agency members to understand, document, and coordinate with/around their efforts.','recZ8ZgEq9ql8hWiL, recNTBiQy4J1sTHdt, rec0BbSfh3O9rsmyu, rec8Ni8drv8Y7ZnCo','recEo6wrqK4qY2kTJ, reciEQnCjzAG4u5Pe','','','',''),(21,'recR9XQpbQlGcRa78','agriculture','glossary','','','rec624EGIiwOXFdeF','','','',''),(22,'recxUQr3otn21zWLc','air pollution data','glossary','','','recpltjn3OiHSTxsl','','','',''),(23,'recK8hhRErBNbaq7h','Alerting','glossary','','','reccxVokbChIm1u6k','','','',''),(24,'recmf60SAsRCAtgMQ','alternative','glossary','