humanitarian sector, some potential use cases for blockchain technology are in information management,\nidentification, supply chain tracking, cash programming and humanitarian financing.\nâ€¢  Since blockchain technology can offer solutions to existing humanitarian challenges, it may be wise to begin studying its\nimpact and experimenting with future implementation.','recaWwiI1AQZmD5PT, reclpdzG4gwRFdpf4, recf6S6Gaq96ssg0D, recuMK1SNZCzbChyd, recdT6TPxki7IkhK7, recofmjQDs9iDPwV8, recPgQMcOwD25qEEl, recRDog1sdTeCDJIv','recrGmD7qytwnEDhr, reccLbN6iNKHEIztp, recuDAeIiOAoo7hVH, recrJncc0rqIWmM4g, rechDlo4ftvvf2tvr, reciKcdM9HNUrYVoa, recIfXfmOVvRNe2ID, reckhoZ6vj3ekOVqR','','','','blockchain'),(62,'recRDog1sdTeCDJIv','Blockchain for Humanitarians Use','Recommendations','Capitalize on existing research and development: Block-chain technology is already having a profound impact on how private companies manage data, interact with custom-ers and pursue innovation.52 The humanitarian sector can leverage this existing knowledge to adapt the technology for humanitarian needs. This also involves creating incentives for the private sector to invest in research and development that benefits the humanitarian space. The humanitarian community can also partner with Governments and com-panies already working in this area (Estonia, Delaware, UK), as well as with the blockchain open-source community and non-profits in the blockchain space, such as COALA, IPDB and Blockstack.Build on existing infrastructure: There are several differ-ent blockchain platforms that can be adapted to humanitari-an use cases. The sector can partner with existing blockchain platforms, such as Ethereum, to build pilot projects for small-er and specific test applications.Similarly, those interested in implementing blockchain can look to previous instances of new technology being adopted in the humanitarian sector. For instance, humanitarian actors can look to the adoption of mobile banking as an example of how the blockchain and digital currencies can be adapted to humanitarian needs. Actors could also investigate leveraging existing infrastructure, such as mobile banking infrastructure, to enable blockchain applications.Research the humanitarian applications of blockchain technology: The humanitarian sector needs research and development to further investigate how blockchain technol-ogy can be adapted to address humanitarian challenges. The above use cases are just some of the potential applications of blockchain technology in the sector. More careful research into the benefits, challenges and consequences of using the technology should be pursued. Furthermore, additional re-search and evidence are needed to translate these potential use cases to actual implementation. Once clear use cases are established in other sectors, the humanitarian sector should adapt best practices and lessons learned from other sec-tors to translate the blockchain to humanitarian purposes. Research organizations, such as the Overseas Development Institute, can build and test prototypes of humanitarian-spe-cific blockchain applications.Create basic frameworks for understanding and using blockchain technology: If blockchain technology is to be implemented in the humanitarian sector, guidelines for safety, security and data sharing must be established. Best practices and guidance for using data responsibly must be adopted, which can then be used to develop a framework to use the blockchain responsibly. These policies must be developed and agreed on by all actors using the technology. For instance, this may involve creating minimum data-usage standards for blockchain-enabled information sharing. The Humanitarian Data Centre may be one space well suited for further exploration of this.','recdT6TPxki7IkhK7, recofmjQDs9iDPwV8, recaWwiI1AQZmD5PT','reccLbN6iNKHEIztp, recrJncc0rqIWmM4g','recYj5ycLZn9yz0Hk','','',''),(63,'recapuo80HowYlrcM','Blogs â€“ online places where a topic is written about consistently at medium length.','glossary','','','','','','',''),(64,'recp0MapnLVbpPFBV','Branding','Toolboxes','','recxxFZREKJmiblYK, recclHBYARCtgn7F2, recK6y8mwbpqmNKEv','','','','',''),(65,'recnn7KRiX4c2P6Dj','branding','glossary','','','recMspjDoOBLESkb8','','','',''),(66,'recGzhIajI9pDcg9L','brasil','glossary','','','rec2R4s1ASXtqj14k','','','',''),(67,'recHjNE2lesKWycST','browser clinical apps','glossary','','','recV79kiLPFKfcaiL','','','',''),(68,'recSEvpULUnb5ASlT','Budgets','data','Implement a project within the constraints of access to resources.','recgtHhKhQbNQ0Uzw','','','','',''),(69,'recaUqsN2hAOBIKjk','Build or access 3W (who is doing what, where)','Tasks','Build or access 3W (who is doing what, where)','rec40sH1svojf9xpJ','','','','',''),(70,'rec40sH1svojf9xpJ','Build situational awareness.','Toolboxes','','rec1iOl4gCxYFBu9x, recHYU7EruNHc0k42, recaUqsN2hAOBIKjk, recI7xh7DRy9F0IeT, rec5sUzBvFWoOQFdj','','','','',''),(71,'recvM22to5b8GhqjU','building infrastructures','glossary','','','rec3hwS1GjNy3eghU','','','',''),(72,'recXvn81TMfNYgaoH','Calendar','Tool Type','','','recs42NAQExDmy03e, recRTPZoVwHQihmbw','','','','calendar'),(73,'recFaSrlsTI2cRa6H','Call Detail Records','data','Invade people\'s privacy by tracking their location, contacts, contents of SMS, details about applications used.','recbfysdXK931PXXh','','','','',''),(74,'recY1PRGXAFq36jwl','Camp Management','Sector','','','','','','',''),(75,'reczI7DkzxDUZtdp0','Canvassing','Challenges','One of the best ways to collect information from people affected by disaster is via door-to-door canvassing of residents. Finding and training volunteers and asking the right questions of residents will be keys to a successful canvass.','recW4gfJIWhRniBIg, rec1N4BMHzDqAzNnp, recYMbCtiPLmAtyHW, recEopnY7PKEilO7q','','','','',''),(76,'recdeMMGRPb23AFOI','canvassing','Skills','','','','','','',''),(77,'recYMbCtiPLmAtyHW','Canvassing Data Model','Toolboxes','Before you begin to canvass affected residents and businesses, you need to know what questions to ask. And, you need to know how you\'ll structure the answers: multiple choice? Yes/no? etc.\n\nIn order to turn the valuable information you\'re collecting into usable data, you\'ll need to ask the same set of questions of each person you canvass. Being intentional about the data model you use before you begin canvassing will save you a lot of data merging headaches down the line.','recjjyxfA2BlPRyve, reczI7DkzxDUZtdp0','','','','',''),(78,'recEopnY7PKEilO7q','Canvassing Training','Toolboxes','Churches, schools and other organizations are often the best resources for doing large-scale canvassing: they can mobilize big groups of people for one or two days at a time, and a bounded task like canvassing often feels rewarding and manageable for one-time volunteers. In order to make the most effective use of these volunteers\' time, you will need quick, easy-to-understand training materials that can get volunteers up to speed and into the field as fast as possible.','reczI7DkzxDUZtdp0','','','','',''),(79,'recs4vKlwc5BKI45r','Capacity Building','data','','','','','','',''),(80,'rec7OGinZAOtv7liS','Capacity Building','Tags','','recSLHAxbavwLcnbE','recfAhD0tAcdvhjAI, rec2lZY26CUz7sVWb, recxBIz2Qgwr2O7qH, rec680XZ7WTeTalO2, rec3G3cfzNDTsNbEH, reciUltv9KjTTW2jy, rec81T0xYbBksAmuZ','recPe6KJYNgkrQrpP, reciSb262hMYonuqD','','',''),(81,'rec8atOKATtCtH1zq','capture','glossary','','','rechbISJhFEySprVr','','','',''),(82,'rechRM6Mk5F2Mw0FV','Case Management','Toolboxes','Case Management is the coordination of services on behalf of those who have been affected by a disaster. It involves understanding people\'s needs and navigating the landscape of services that can help them meet those needs.\n\n\"Case Management\" is a federally regulated term in disaster relief.  It is supposed to be used to describe a very specific type of activity in which an \"official\" disaster case manager gives assistance to an individual person whom they manage.\n\nWhat makes someone an official \"disaster case manager\"? One factor is their ability to access the CAN disaster case management system - the official case management system of the Red Cross. But, since CiviCRM is now powerful enough to support disaster case management use cases as well, the access barrier has been reduced.','recNmMk2QPPkX908b, recdZk6CZiTywlVag, recHADIjSyUNfQX7M, recfC03GSAMAdwx0B, recHZ9ezebt2edVRc, recjjyxfA2BlPRyve, recEtIwLKglEs5fjQ','','','','',''),(83,'recHZ9ezebt2edVRc','Case Management with CiviCRM','Tutorials','The CiviCase component of CiviCRM enables users to create cases and take them through different workflows depending on that caseâ€™s unique situation. For example, someone who got has their claim denied by their insurance company would go through a multi-step process of finding a lawyer, submitting an appeal, and receiving a response, while someone who needs to have their house rebuilt would go through the stages of being assessed, being scheduled, having work begin, having it end, etc. Each of these multistage processes would be configured beforehand.\n\nYou can also use CiviCRM\'s tagging structure to do a basic type of case management.  You can learn more about Tracking Correspondence with CiviCRM.\n\nWe donâ€™t currently have documentation for how to configure CiviCase for disasters so thatâ€™s on our to-do list for Phase II of this project.\n','rechRM6Mk5F2Mw0FV, recdZk6CZiTywlVag','recZHSZypSFHafKIW','','','',''),(84,'rechr1s1HEVaxvfdy','Case studies','Tags','','','','','','',''),(85,'recriocokIMoNHNZf','Case Studies â€“ summary of how something happened.','glossary','','','','','','',''),(86,'recOwn40QDPvvWvqP','Case studies about the use of World Pop data','Tags','','','','','','',''),(87,'reckYmt4y3L1MlaJD','Case study of privacy/issues from big data in ebola response','Tags','','','','','','',''),(88,'recPgQMcOwD25qEEl','Cash Programming','Toolboxes','Cash-based programming is a widely employed technology among humanitarian actors and is expected to rise in the future. \n\nBlockchain technology can be leveraged to support and address challenges in using centralized databases, ensuring data security and sharing information across multiple actors.\n\nDigital cash has been highlighted as a key recommendation\nfor cash-programme practitioners. 43/44 The Overseas Devel-\nopment Institute High-Level Panel on Humanitarian Cash\nTransfers recommends â€œwhere possible, deliver cash digitally and in a manner that enhances further financial inclusion.â€ 45\nDigital cash and payments are recommended as they en-\nsure greater transparency around how much aid reaches\naffected populations, make payments cheaper, increase\nsecurity and accelerate financial inclusion. 46 As cash transfers often rely on digital technology, considerations on data-exchange standards, data security, privacy and encryption are critical to the process. 48 The use of cen-\ntralized databases is another challenge, as cash program-\nming allows for more connected programming. The block-\nchain may address these considerations. A shared platform\nbased on the blockchain can allow humanitarian actors to\neasily and responsibly share population and usage trends\nand anonymized transaction data. Digital cash payments\ncan be made traceable, interoperable across multiple actors,\nmore secure and at a lower cost through blockchain technol-\nogy, with the possibility of tracking funds from original donor\nto final recipient while still ensuring privacy and security. 49','recr7GNJJiUL0nTrx','','','','',''),(89,'recJhvzdNTks6LNFz','Central Data Repository','Toolboxes','Quite often, the most critical information that needs to be shared during disaster relief and recovery comes in the form of files such as spreadsheets and PDFs. These files may contain crucial relief information that should be made as publicly available as possible. Or, they might contain sensitive data that should only be accessible to a specific group of people.\n\n\n