er they\'re online or in print, are easiest to put together when their authors have streams of relevant content, ideally republishable/syndicatable content, coming into  a single place tool that they can then use to organize and share that content.\n','recSdjmCIqv1XizV8, recQZtGMy5sgFvIRi, recBVRfkIofP8OE8l, reckwIXsOhNYd88py, recK6y8mwbpqmNKEv','','','','',''),(177,'recK6y8mwbpqmNKEv','Content Publishing','Challenges','Getting information flowing through the organs of your relief group is essential for keeping your communications platforms up to date.\n\nYou\'ll need some internal communication systems in place to make sure the right information is featured. \n\nYou will also need need external communcations channels and a strategy that uses  your messaging to achieve specific goals of your group or organizaiton.  ','recwhC0BDxCv2XmOF, recp0MapnLVbpPFBV, recYyj1U8W8quyzhz, recdiL5Rb4ZicrIfC, recUAPmfMcKTC46RP, recSw7FzVZSOba0M0, recI1bc212RVK7aKK, rec3NEj4ZcZ6KT0hA','rec9KuFLn69nVvWS9, recYBznRKPggkKrzU','','','',''),(178,'recdiL5Rb4ZicrIfC','Content Team','Toolboxes','Producing consistent, high quality content requires a team of committed people.\n\nThe primary tasks of a \"content team\" is to:\n\nwrite copy for the primary communication channels such as a website, email newsletter and printed materials.\nmanage a calendar of events\ncorrespond with the community via public email address, social media, text loop\nestablish a process whereby people can get their information publish through communications channels\nevaluate, curate and publish appropriate information\nAside from performing the tasks above, the content team will also have to make difficult decisions about what information to post and who to trust. In adhoc and grassroots operations, this might mean that the people who manage content on the website are the ultimate decision-makers about what constituents \"official\" statements and communcations to the outside world. This often includes the official donation page/process and the official contact info for media/press, partner organizations, volunteers, etc.  \n\nIf the roster, roles and responsibilities of the content team aren\'t clearly defined then it\'s likely that tasks will fall through the cracks and critical decisions about fundraising and media relations will either be handled poorly or not handled at all.\n','recK6y8mwbpqmNKEv','','','','',''),(179,'rec25f4VqXq0n8JMN','Contract','Tags','','recu9BqjQViflaxC9','','','','',''),(180,'rec14GvxnUyQQ183Y','Contract','glossary','','','rec5ZUNbF89Aue5OJ, recHeRzlyvI6CJlm5','','','',''),(181,'recR19V6gfOhjPJ8X','Contributing to this Website','Toolboxes','Sign up for an account here. Once you have an account you can edit existing \"cards\" or creating new ones by clicking your desired card types in the \"Add\" menu on the right side of the page under the main logo.\n','recVaSue3xHMSKyy0, recPKIqmXWSiJRxzY','','','','',''),(182,'recSbYtGJvFWKhzd2','conventional and renewable energy technologies','glossary','','','receqqigIUe2Hm5lw','','','',''),(183,'recwfq6oYZkqaCbDW','cooking','glossary','','','recqPkDhp14BArq8P','','','',''),(184,'recKu56HZr9A2UoLv','Coordinate with other warehouses and organizations for load balancing','Workflows','','reckNyxDnvAtVO82p, recZoqL43IBjFlcAZ','','','','Willow',''),(185,'recZjjj5j5FcsxfAU','Coordinating Physical Resources','Challenges','A moderately-sized disaster relief group has to manage the inflow of goods and in-kind donations after a storm. This inventory might arrive at multiple locations and need to be distributed to a wide variety of facilities, including other warehouses, informal and formal relief hubs, and relief sites located in affected communities. Tracking the movement of goods is critical in order to ensure that they get where they need to beâ€”and, in some cases, in order to meet donor requirements or government regulations.','recnebUtIIFB2MmCh, recoo0FF7LYlbK8Ge, recEzW5HwohYyLj9N, recmFBM3jsCvmbqtC, recerWLHj3n60GIuS','','','','',''),(186,'recmpIjtnQjN70nAK','Coordinating Rebuild','Challenges','Disasters wreak major havoc on communities. Individual homes, shared community space, public infrastructure, civic institutions and businesses can suffer significant damage, making it difficult for people to move on.\n\nCoordinating rebuild requires a lot of different people to work together. You need information from needs assessment to figure out what to rebuild, volunteers who are ready, willing and able to do the work, resource management to bring the right tools and materials to the right place at the right time, and of course, a lot of network coordination to ensure that some people and projects aren\'t falling through the cracks while others double or triple dip into available resources.','recnebUtIIFB2MmCh, recoo0FF7LYlbK8Ge, recmFBM3jsCvmbqtC, recPmiDdEzFnEhiNM','','','','',''),(187,'recRAxhTdgNtLpaOW','Coordination','Tool Type','works on how different actors overlap while in action','','','','','','coordination'),(188,'recZ8ZgEq9ql8hWiL','Coordination','Use Case','','rec6AG7gOqhuPt0IS','recSPdAS4NhwePhPU, reczlCkRoVPppsncS','','','',''),(189,'recKpqvpwgRAwwUDp','coordination','glossary','','','recofJnN2a0np4Z7L','','','',''),(190,'receRzr12fzaTSbBz','Coordination - Cross-Sectoral','Tags','','','recEkTJyfxi3Nw2wz','recjmXiZRTpO1irgT, rec5Mtj3HPOz5OZIt','','',''),(191,'reckNyxDnvAtVO82p','Coordination - Deployment','Tags','','recvEAD2lwzuM3x7r, recQb1iriEZd7d8vB, recKu56HZr9A2UoLv, recutVU6cRqBvkqeM, recuberEW8ckHB1aW, recrtwIaECwhZS33r, rec6AG7gOqhuPt0IS, recMwIUWKB7oWF5mB','recw81WL03uD2ChQL, reczlCkRoVPppsncS, recNbhQ3Gub0hRm3I','rechmgbW09SdwyUIo, rec5XPSluRUXlNxuI, rec727818eSfLKkRw','','',''),(192,'rec7kcEKB7N2hFzpa','Coordination - Inter-Organizational','Tags','','','recc47QxDduLbjcYw','','','',''),(193,'recKYK3Nevj59YUiH','cop watch','Skills','','','','','','',''),(194,'recGrS1TogvTFSiTW','Counts','glossary','running tallies where 0 is a meaningful number','rechRB9PU22N3clgo','','','','',''),(195,'recWpvhmhyn1Lesu7','Create a Collaborative Inbox','Tutorials','During disasters, email inboxes can overflow, creating communication backlogs that force people to miss important opportunities.  It doesnâ€™t need to be that way.  You forward emails from a general email address and from your own to a shared inbox, enabling multiple people to view the messages, answer emails from a common address and track whether emails have been address.','recFmTEL3UuvxzYJz','recUiHoYSXjwhqwsl','','','',''),(196,'recynNv0zpMM5J6p6','Create a Listserv','Tutorials','Your group or organizations should have an email listserv (ex. Google Group) where members can receive important emails.  It can be configured so only group owners or moderators can send messages to everyone, or so that all can talk to all.  Either way, a clear, common communication channel is critical.  \n\n\nProtip: You can share a Google Folder (collaborative documents) with everyone in a Google Group simply by using the Google Groupâ€™s email address.  This allows you to manage access to your Google Folder by managing access to your Google Group.','recFmTEL3UuvxzYJz','recUiHoYSXjwhqwsl','','','',''),(197,'recee1gL6OMXXUKPF','create tracking system','glossary','','','rec84uFTp7pUVQh4R','','','',''),(198,'rec31FCztnFm0NNgB','Creating Aerial Imagery','Tasks','Take aerial imagery','recDfY2UZj521EIWn, recReqN39G0tE5lvn','','','','',''),(199,'recKQnJ4kdJ60Gcmj','CRM','Tool Type','Constituent Relationship Management systems are databases that collect and organize information about people who want to interact with and/or receive more information about a groupâ€™s activities. When this information is entered into a database, it can be â€œqueriedâ€ (i.e. searched) in useful ways that make communication much easier.  Most CRMs are focused on providing solutions to businesses, but a few are oriented towards nonprofit and community groups. They provide a wide range of relationship management and engagement solutions.\n\nCRMs have the capacity to provide similar functionality as an Help Desk, but they often arenâ€™t configured to do so â€œout-of-the-boxâ€, and when they are configured to do so, they often present a more complicated and difficult to use alternative to a help desk system.  However, since CRMs have the ability to provide case management services, it might be practical to use it for correspondence tacking.  ','recFN89wM7ldOSmK8, reczOawjZjmMmuUDy, recwCY7kOuRqdQTuB, rechRM6Mk5F2Mw0FV, recdcveRb1arT5kZU, rec15Oy0yXmnuAmQU, rec7QyiwnW3f8BbLO, reczM0xmBmCLRGbNg, recpVBOwWc6KExU4T, recfxxooUSe9kdOPu, recmeOAEqc9mtVNTq, recLvTMjhzXrnq6UR, recHZ9ezebt2edVRc, recHADIjSyUNfQX7M, recfC03GSAMAdwx0B','recZHSZypSFHafKIW, recJq44xhzpIQvqyi','','','','crm'),(200,'recdZk6CZiTywlVag','CRM','glossary','','','recZHSZypSFHafKIW','','','',''),(201,'recfC03GSAMAdwx0B','CRM Software Recommendations','Recommendations','CRM (customer/constituent relationship management) systems are designed to help a large and physically dispersed group of people collect information about individuals and groups, record interactions and document outcomes.  This type of system is very useful for disaster relief groups because it helps them manage relationships with four types of people:\n\nvolunteers who want to give their time\ndonors who want to give their money\nsurvivors who need assistance\nhuman service providers who can help people in need\nA few VOAD member groups that I spoke with were using CRMs for their Sandy relief operations â€” but, by and large, the VOAD community isn\'t using CRMs.\n\nInstead, most VOAD members I spoke with were either using spreadsheets or desktop-based database systems to track and manage their relationships.\n\nThe few organizations that were using the CAN system for disaster case management  lacked a solution for the CRM functions CAN doesn\'t provide, such as volunteer and donor management.\n\n More About CAN\n\nThe general sentiment about CAN at the NVOAD event was that itâ€™s an outdated piece of software, but itâ€™s the best thing the communityâ€™s got. Even still, few organizations use it voluntarily and was widely cited as one of the largest bottlenecks to effective disaster case management, especially during the first months of the disaster when few people who were doing case management work could access the system.\n\nSome of the problems with CAN articulated during the NVOAD event include:\n\nIt takes days, sometimes weeks, to be granted access to CAN; and many grassroots relief groups and some VOAD member groups simply donâ€™t qualify for access. Many groups waste time and energy trying to access CAN when they could be using those resources to develop and deploy CRM systems that meet their own unique set of needs.\nAll data that goes into CAN becomes the property of the Red Cross under terms that are difficult to question or change.\nOnly CAN employees and CAN partners can perform import and export functions.\nNo one but VisionLink can modify the CAN software.','rechRM6Mk5F2Mw0FV, recdcveRb1arT5kZU','recZHSZypSFHafKIW, recJq44xhzpIQvqyi','','','Devin',''),(202,'recN4X9qU9TT5yrhl','Crowd Sourcing','data','','','','recBj69JiVzkhxYbq','','',''),(203,'recOoI8V6MEw21bw8','Crowd Sourcing','Tags','','recCHPp5tbhtSbGwE','reca1xhnj9VGmdqfG','','','',''),(204,'recr5j3rtEZmYX4W9','crowd-funding','glossary','','','recErG2MUxANSWBJk','','','',''),(205,'recofmjQDs9iDPwV8','Crowdfunding','Toolboxes','Blockchain technology can be used for crowdfunding and\nmicrofinancing in emergencies in two ways: through using\nexisting digital currencies and by providing a decentralized\nfunding platform.\nOCHAâ€™s Crowdfunding for Emergencies Think Brief reports\nthat â€œincreasing transparency, accountability and reporting\namong donors, project initiators and funding recipients increases trust in the project and ensures continued donor\nengagement.â€50 Harnessing the blockchain can increase this\ntransparency, accountability and trust by providing a verifiable\nplatform.\nExisting crowdfunding programs already use Bitcoin and other\ncryptocurrencies to fund humanitarian emergencies. Examples\ninclude Colu, BTC Funding, CoinFunder and BitPesa.\nThese platforms have lower transaction costs, which ensures\ntransparent and rapid disbursement of funds during crises.\nMoreover, these crowdfunding initiatives can go beyond\ndigital currencies, such as Bitcoin. Where previously a centralized\nservice, such as Indiegogo, was needed to enable a\ncrowdfunding campaign, crowdfunding platforms powered\nby blockchain technology remove the need for an intermediary\nthird party to monitor and disburse funds. These\nplatforms use blockchain technology to reduce transaction\ncosts and enable rapid disbursement of micropayments. As\nfunds are processed on a peer-to-peer basis, funds raised can\nbe approved and transferred directly to the recipients. The\nhumanitarian sector could establish its own dedicated cryptocurrency,\nsuch as AidCoin, to reduce transaction times and\nexchange-rate losses while maintaining transparency and\ntraceability of funds.51','recr7GNJJiUL0nTrx, recRDog1sdTeCDJIv, recclHBYARCtgn7F2, recyu9NYKDDxJRLCA','','','','',''),(206,'recearlCBa3Q2xVvZ','culturally diverse','glossary','','','recWiEy3n8ld1QOMt','','','',''),(207,'recDOMzMjPTlqYQ17','Curating News and Events for Newsletters','Tutorials','They can be especially useful for producing newsletters.  Newsletters are easiest to put together when their authors have streams of content coming into a single place.  For example, if you\'re writing a newsletter to a community affected by a disaster, it\'s useful to collect and view newsfeeds from organizations active in that disaster.  When you see an item that the newsletter community might be interested in, you can then include that item in the newsletter.  To do this, simply collect the news (RSS) and event (iCAL) from all the individuals and groups who want to be featured in your newsletter.\n','recI1bc212RVK7aKK, recFmTEL3UuvxzYJz','recbgLoJeve3wuH6N, recNd3gafKgzajz6a, recn2Fe6mUozKtlNU','','','',''),(208,'recmskKsd9przLMdx','customizable','glossary','','','reckPinv92dotkoBH','','','',''),(209,'rec8GnMArqIRC7mWw','customizable at no cost','glossary','','','rec1Mnq16feoRzxUH','','','',''),(210,'recaMy9QK9jdqJ8FU','Damage Assessment','Toolboxes','Damage assessment - determining where to send limited resources.','','','','','',''),(211,'recReqN39G0tE5lvn','Damage assessment - determining where to send limited resources.','Toolboxes','','recjBVDcyTKNYxM9u, recrrwRiAcXVTz7Q9, recxJi83l7ILjQ1s9, recjmUHCv55loAt5j, recEy7nfXXdLHJrX7, recS9kHmJWubiTS4c, recCHPp5tbhtSbGwE, recNTBiQy4J1sTHdt, recYeh9IOchuEygO2, recuonNXVQCAV91A8, recqFKhShTLzHRUIe, rec31FCztnFm0NNgB, rec0BbSfh3O9rsmyu, recCIw9j0UVrrTFGf','','','','',''),(212,'recS9kHmJWubiTS4c','Damage Assessment using Canvassing','Tasks','Walk around marking on a map what is damaged, and to what degree','recqVYJyuOteg4eEF, recReqN39G0tE5lvn','','','','',''),(213,'recCHPp5tbhtSbGwE','Damage Assessment using Imagery','Tasks','Identify and mark areas of damaged infrastructure in an image','recOoI8V6MEw21bw8, recReqN39G0tE5lvn','','','','',''),(214,'recsBlntwidq42Ynk','data','Skills','','','','','','',''),(215,'recO4rj0Tl4nOC5IA','data','glossary','','','recEfLIUcee7xk0ft, recNOVsIJmDwZiI7e, recPcd5CegMRTlHeq, rec9vAHeUzYCFMvQY','','','',''),(216,'rec3IaYREHCmWqwre','data','glossary','','rechRB9PU22N3clgo, recRv5bByhmET1Ncz, recPOhN4DXWRMmYOy, recx0kY1CvEJSkbnm, recy9bOMa0tDoHhsN, rec8teGY7CnU71x1J, recmcvikkjkcXOkwY, recAthyUz5MFleB3K, recSEvpULUnb5ASlT, recfzSIcI0HCmL5uq, recrONMGyKFnwTOhf, recbW0cUxwFDCvRfX, recFaSrlsTI2cRa6H, reczWyUlwJdIphLOq, recLy08xrAyPk6uZm, recrp7Z1anRl89i0s, recme7gn4qSchYhDm, recXAVByqbQQPHx4q, rec3x2wFL96ycvBsa, reckaDnQkHKr7Tdbb, rec0YJGoEQ3yZTUSo, recHjAGJjAQxL0naU, rec5s6dhq2DaMOwud, recIMA1ty9QITjcq5, reccwyD5w4bF3DHzb, recivIO7uSXZZFKug, recVT5ceZuPq8NGKO, recJRHDHvmFYmTF35, rec7OGinZAOtv7liS, recgtHhKhQbNQ0Uzw, recdyMXuPO8WyCKH1, recmKsyAUwHIqdFY9, recWNX91VUaintM4q, recfkl31XeNDUIIqz, recq6zCRgVjaHfNaQ, recDfY2UZj521EIWn, recLDfkyaF3ywJJjv, recMYPmwDqhL6ILXw, recOoI8V6MEw21bw8, recqVYJyuOteg4eEF','recyWXZpcDrbDgs80','','','',''),(217,'rec3bSaPxZDbjO7mZ','data about refugees','Tags','','','','','','',''),(218,'reczPF8xOB2r9sh5A','data aggregation','glossary','','','recEOFP1tUQ1gAN25','','','',''),(219,'recpN9880PyyxG7u9','Data Analysis','Tool Type','','','reck36VqMMVoPb1Lh, recdtCdehJaBRURZM','','','','data-analysis'),(220,'recFRFM2NYLfbJ2fI','Data Analysis','glossary','','','recbQU1FJFnoX29no','','','',''),(221,'rec1Rkw6n1i2e16zy','data analysis','glossary','','','rec1o6ZzZrW4I294J, recHteUVQ9M3BXV7w, rechbISJhFEySprVr, recnoFKzDM8lDs1VQ, recropIQtMDYenT5W','','','',''),(222,'rec49xhLoQZDMmSdn','data analysis and management','glossary','','','reclmAm6bGKBDD6wm','','','',''),(223,'recyRbCqHpWCKoo8X','Data Assets','Tool Type','','','rec9vAHeUzYCFMvQY, recyWXZpcDrbDgs80, recM4zDr2GtcyKGCH','','','','data-assets'),(224,'rechdqzwV4rShiA2Q','Data Collection','Tool Type','','','rec4rTTDHxNrTLzMS','','','','data-collection'),(225,'recqWTMS42QcS8GAO','data collection','glossary','','','rec1o6ZzZrW4I294J, recHteUVQ9M3BXV7w, reclmAm6bGKBDD6wm, recEOFP1tUQ1gAN25, recBRw30Cs2zjBsle, rec9vAHeUzYCFMvQY, recyWXZpcDrbDgs80, recYkbG5VBmP3FDbf, recm8egn2fT29Gonr, rec4rTTDHxNrTLzMS','','','',''),(226,'recw2CdPRVDKjisQW','data extraction','glossary','','','recpTo6YSbFVOQnWJ, recEOFP1tUQ1gAN25','','','',''),(227,'recSdjmCIqv1XizV8','Data Formats','Tool Type','Format describes the type of file being managed. Examples of different electronic formats include PDF, CSV, TXT, XLS, XML, etc.\n\nFor resources to be easily shared online, they must be in the same or compatible formats. Some formats are easier to share offline than others.  The chart below shows a list of popular formats with rankings from (1) worst to (3) best.\n\nhttps://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/u/2/d/1z3yO5bTWUMabCj6ko2KQQN8TPx6h5WgkroKAZeNs16A/pub?output=html&widget=true\n\nPDFs are great for printing but make it nearly impossible to share their data with other systems.  \nCSVs are fantastic for sharing data but almost entirely unintelligible in print.  \nThe best formats for sharing news and events information is through XML formats.  Most popular website content management systems (CMS) produce XML news feeds called RSS and event feeds call iCAL. Google Calendars also produce iCAL feeds.','recSw7FzVZSOba0M0, recwCY7kOuRqdQTuB, rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I, recYyj1U8W8quyzhz, recBVRfkIofP8OE8l','recNd3gafKgzajz6a, recn2Fe6mUozKtlNU','','','','data-formats'),(228,'recU4b4g8PUVdpx7y','Data Governance','Tool Type','For a data standard to remain relevant and useful, the community that uses it should be able to update the standard to meet their ever changing needs.  For them to do this effectively, standards should be managed by a body (group of people) and they should provide people with the ability to modify the standard.','rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I','','','','','data-governance'),(229,'recZRbn5QmpueyEpv','data integration','glossary','','','recpTo6YSbFVOQnWJ','','','',''),(230,'rect3p4UVY9fu3bnb','Data Liscensing','Tool Type','If you want information to be as accessible and useful as possible while still retaining legal control over the information, a creative commons licenses should be used.  These are many different types.  You can learn more here: http://creativecommons.org/choose/','rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I','','','','','data-liscensing'),(231,'recBxfdUX5nrWayrm','data management','Skills','','','','','','',''),(232,'recrqOOQlCsG9eso3','data management','glossary','','','recpTo6YSbFVOQnWJ','','','',''),(233,'recznbHIfPxQYv42D','Data Management Best Practices','Tutorials','If your organization or coalition wants to organize information resources for itself and it\'s constituencies then there are a few things to keep in mind:\n\n \nAudience\nThe first step should be to define your audience(s).  Most \"network coordination\" groups (ex. LTROs) in New York City, have three distinct audiences.\n\nSurvivors.  These are the people who\'re looking to your group for support.\nCollaborators.  These are the people who are internal to your organization or group, or are a peer group which whom your group shares information. Ex. A volunteer recruitment committee.\nSpecialists.  These are people who you want to help provide a specific service.  Ex. Disaster Case Managers.\nIt\'s important to think about a few traits of each audience:\n\nThrough what mediums (web, flier, telephone) does this audience receive information? How can you organize information so it\'s easiest to display through all relevant mediums?\nCan anyone access the resources you\'re sharing with this audience, or must access be controlled?  \n \nAccess Control\nBefore you decide access must be controlled to a certain set of information, ask yourself why you believe this.  \n\nWill the public availability of this information put anyone at risk?  If so, how?  If not:\nHas access to this information been controlled in the past because it was impractical to share it with the world or because people were worried that releasing this information would make their job harder or different?  If so, consider whether or not access really needs to be controlled.\nIf access must be controlled, then:\n\nWho determines who can access the information?  For example, if information can only be shared with DCMs, how will you know if someone is a DCM?  Or, if information can only be shared with members of the LTRO, how will you determine is people are members? \n\nThrough what mechanism will be control access? Are you using a system in which people have to log in to access information?  If so, recognize that people are SIGNIFICANTLY less likely to access information if they have to log in to access it.  If you\'re simply sending a digital document to people but not limiting others from accessing it, consider whether the information really shouldn\'t be publicly available.','rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I, rec6tfo141ypk7g7y, rec5AIxShAcopknOE, recNmMk2QPPkX908b','','','','',''),(234,'recpSbQd2wbRhAb7e','Data Management Best Practices','Toolboxes','','recNa2BkIDTmwIxzJ, recyxPGtBLZZvtnSC','','','','',''),(235,'recyxPGtBLZZvtnSC','Data Management Software Recommendations','Recommendations','At the most basic level, groups engaged in disaster relief and community resilience work should have access to a Dropbox-like file sharing system which can host both public and private files and folder systems. OwnCloud is an easy-to-deploy, easy-to-use system that could meet this need.\n\nIf a group or network wants to make it easy for its member organizations to benefit from the open data revolution, they can set up a CKAN â€œdata repositoryâ€, which provides groups with the ability to upload, describe, preview, download, host and stream a wide variety of data formats. It can be used to host and organize PDFs, turn CSVs (spreadsheets) into interactive maps and serve dynamic data streams in real time to other software applications. For the more technically ambitious, it can also wrap data in an API with which software developers can use to create applications, produce visualizations and build semantic information resources.\n\nDisaster relief groups could use a data repository to share a wide variety of data and knowledge information, including:\n\ninformation about affected areas, such as demographics, geography/geology, environmental reports, important places, and mapping layers\ncanvassing data related to individual and neighbourhood needs for things like food, shelter, and health care\nraw data about who is providing disaster relief and which populations they are serving\ntemplates for managing inventory, work sites, damage assessment surveys, volunteer registration forms and other tools for disaster relief groups\nhow-to\'s and trainings guides about everything from killing mold to anonymizing and responsibly sharing data\nData repositories allow users to upload both public data that can be shared with everyone, and private data that can be managed by particular users without anyone else seeing it. To prevent confidential information from being made public, the system can be configured such that all public data uploads are moderated, and only approved data sets are made public. In such a configuration, when users find incorrect data or data that shouldn\'t be shared on the system, they can flag it as inappropriate so it can be taken offline. Of course, with more data tools available, it would be incumbent on the relief community to learn more about how to use data and data tools to improve their operations.','recpSbQd2wbRhAb7e','recfQ73YS5ym7AA52, recGh8kwoHhb5rBsN','','','Devin',''),(236,'recHYTfoWM2YfliY7','Data Manager','Use Case','Increase the accuracy of response efforts by managing incoming data from (and contributing back to) external sources such as Standby Task Force and Humanitarian Data Exchange.','rec67LQ7smpAw91Gt, recP7Q5fU0jHGR9gu, recQb1iriEZd7d8vB, recOnO3n3CM0xFhOJ, recqFKhShTLzHRUIe, reco8HaWarMBJGL6X','recybzxcMsGWbv8Px, recyEjBHi7dIGSqyI','recSgxPcpqEuYJJW0','','',''),(237,'recV82w4J8zfNaaXN','data pipeline','glossary','','','recpTo6YSbFVOQnWJ','','','',''),(238,'recRe40HLKnQTjYKK','data portal','glossary','','','recoxM9POOYtkW78t','','','',''),(239,'recFfMkWgIL9n3mSu','data prediction','glossary','','','recpTo6YSbFVOQnWJ','','','',''),(240,'rec9La5JA8s53gek8','Data Repository','Tool Type','A data repository system allows users to upload both (i) private data that they can manage without anyone else seeing it, and (ii) public data that can be shared with everyone. To prevent confidential information from being made public, all public data uploads can be moderated such that only approved datasets are made public. If users find incorrect dataâ€”or data that shouldnâ€™t be shared on the systemâ€”they could flag the dataset as inappropriate and it can be taken offline  Of course, with more data tools available, it is incumbent upon the system\'s implementers to train their community to use data and data tools in responsible ways to improve their operations.','recyxPGtBLZZvtnSC','recGh8kwoHhb5rBsN, recfQ73YS5ym7AA52','','','','data-repository'),(241,'recr8pEvE9OvcwwWx','data repository','glossary','','','recGh8kwoHhb5rBsN, rec9vAHeUzYCFMvQY','','','',''),(242,'rec6tfo141ypk7g7y','Data Schema','Tool Type','A schema is the structure of the data.  It outlines all the different facets/fields of information that should be captures about each individual item.  If you think about data as content on a spreadsheet then the schema is first row, which defined the information in all the columns.  \n\nWhen figuring out how to share data with other people and organizations, one of the most important conversation to have is about the labels on the column headers. If you use the same column headers as other resources, it will be much easier for your resources to be integrated with other resources - enable people to search many resources at one time.  Making your resources interoperable with other resources is really important because it will allow fewer people to develop resources and keep them up to date, while producing superior resources for your constituents.','rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I, recpSbQd2wbRhAb7e','','','','','data-schema'),(243,'rec8mZV6GvPtbBajr','data science','glossary','','','reciCqGyov1XYX4vW','','','',''),(244,'rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I','Data Standards','Toolboxes','To create an effective data standard, decisions needs to be made about four main things:','recU4b4g8PUVdpx7y, rect3p4UVY9fu3bnb, recihxFIxHlgim88H, rec6tfo141ypk7g7y, recSdjmCIqv1XizV8, recBVRfkIofP8OE8l, reclThvxgAo3h5oDY, recpSbQd2wbRhAb7e, recjjyxfA2BlPRyve, recEtIwLKglEs5fjQ, reckRvwsJ4rLE7Ul8, recJwGAA0x7TOhQlE','','','','',''),(245,'recD4ps9GNs9oI2Ek','data storage','glossary','','','recf482b7a0YdWa7K','','','',''),(246,'rec31B4uFy6AxksQH','Data Tables','Tool Type','Data Tables hold data in rows and columns, similar to spreadsheets, but enable you to run services such as geocoding (for mapping) and formulas for various types of visualization and analysis.\n','recwCY7kOuRqdQTuB, recdcveRb1arT5kZU, recy4fsU9qsPfeiuF','recDlVHaF9V3t6YtT, recEfLIUcee7xk0ft, recXT2dYnUA3l5mmE','','','','data-tables'),(247,'recihxFIxHlgim88H','Data Taxonomy','Tool Type','Taxonomies consist of a list of descriptive terms that are used to classify and categorize information.  It is useful to think of this as the terms youâ€™d like to be able to filter resources through.  For example, food stamps help people deal overcome hunger, so you might want to attach the term â€œhungerâ€ to a program or service that provides food stamps to people.\n\nJust like with fields, if you use the same taxonomy as other groups doing similar work, it will be much easier for people to maintain resources and for people to find what they\'re looking for.\n\nWith services information, we need two taxonomies: one that describes â€œwhatâ€ the service provides and the other that describes â€œwhoâ€ that service is meant to assist.  We call the â€œwhatâ€ schema â€œservice_typeâ€ and the â€œwhoâ€ schema â€œaudience.â€\n\n* Civic Services Taxonomy\n\nYou\'ll also need to use a taxonomy for locations information such as neighborhoods.  We recommend using NYC\'s official neighborhood list for \n\n* Location Taxonomy','rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I','','','','','data-taxonomy'),(248,'recU79NL9HzfnH8xS','data visualization','glossary','','','recEfLIUcee7xk0ft','','','',''),(249,'recAZTSdkiDgPfajG','Database','glossary','','','recDlVHaF9V3t6YtT','','','',''),(250,'rec3eJjYhtfz4BvIN','database','glossary','','','recVeir6Xl9hAS3Fu, rectDW4pQ5lV32N1t','','','',''),(251,'recywPNU0rGky2SJL','Database Administrator','Use Case','Maximize the impact of any data-using section of your response organization by maintaining the structure and usability of the databases themselve