o spent funds quickly and in transparent ways.\n\nOrganizations that can accept funds over the internet can raise thousands, even millions, of dollars during a disaster event. They can also solicit donations immediately and expand their community of donors.\n\nOrganziations that can document precisely where the funds they raised are being spent will be able to sustain fundraising efforts into the recovery phase and beyond.  They can also develop effective funding criteria, enabling them to shape intiatives that emerge in response to the disaster.','recclHBYARCtgn7F2, recyu9NYKDDxJRLCA, recQPz2gZ3BKFKiAc, recUcBrdtP6gLvowB','','','','',''),(370,'reccnLZYLLTW1umCS','Financial','glossary','related to funds and accounting','recbW0cUxwFDCvRfX, recrONMGyKFnwTOhf, recfzSIcI0HCmL5uq, recSEvpULUnb5ASlT, recAthyUz5MFleB3K','rec9qW0uW0ugxtjtT, rectQqK4mgCHNTLGw','','','',''),(371,'recWL774hB9n2FtTm','Financial Documentation','Toolboxes','Good financial documentation can feel laboriousâ€”it involves recording each transaction and making your records accessible to those who would seek to make sense of them. As time intensive as it can be, however, financial documentation is essential for staying within the law and proving fulfillment of donor intent if you\'re taking in tax-free donations. And whether or not your donations are tax-free, financial documentation is the basis for transparency.\n\n\n\nCreating systems early on to ensure that your funds are tracked will save lots of time and frustration in the long run.','reccBNxz18IZGnMaN, recQPz2gZ3BKFKiAc','','','','',''),(372,'recNKcrxQjV2NUa49','Financial Protocols','Toolboxes','Clear financial protocols take the guesswork out of much financial decisionmaking. This helps maintain trust within your network and engender confidence amongst donors and disaster survivors. It also makes it easier for those who are stewarding funds, as they can move forward confidently knowing that they aren\'t making things up as they go along, and that they have the approval of the larger community.','recHADIjSyUNfQX7M, rec478jcu2UFRzEUL, recQPz2gZ3BKFKiAc','','','','',''),(373,'recF3cwTxSQkvB1Hg','Find an RSS Feed','Tutorials','To find an RSS feed, do the following:\n\nUsing Firefox, go to the Bookmarks Menu and click \"Subscribe to this page\". If you\'re given a number of options, pick the one labelled \'feed\', \'home\', \'main\', etc. Do not pick \'comments.\'\nIf the page that loads is formatted like the one below, then you\'ve found a clean feed.\n8930 medium\nIf the page has lots of code on it, then copy the URL and paste it  into a new Firefox window.  If it gets formatted into a feed like in the image above, then you\'ve got a good feed.\nIf you\'re registering your feed at NYCPrepared Sites, then take this feed URL and paste it into the \"Feed Registration Page\".\n\nNote: Wordpress websites place usually their RSS feed at www.sitename.com/feed by default. So, if you recognize that a site is Wordpress, that\'s a quick way to find the feed.','recpzOIUandf1GDKe, recQZtGMy5sgFvIRi','recn2Fe6mUozKtlNU, reczw76T3mlJpGKRx','','','',''),(374,'rec2ahMA2JPltBIWv','fintech','glossary','','','reczWJ5vpbWvygQsu','','','',''),(375,'recD7sqHsLvywNC3l','FIre','Sector','','','','','','',''),(376,'recf66iyKInhZuRDj','Fiscal Sponsorship','Toolboxes','You can accept tax deductible online donations if you get your project \"fiscally sponsored\" by a tax exempt (501.c.3) organization.\n','recUcBrdtP6gLvowB','','','','',''),(377,'recvrkISCHzMuxlCE','food','Skills','','','','','','',''),(378,'recOeeilrIRsUr2Ar','Food Security','Sector','','','','','','',''),(379,'recGNLNuQQ2N3nB1u','forest management','glossary','','','reccJjBJfLJhwSxlH','','','',''),(380,'rec6MHPin0Uo1B14d','Formats','glossary','Format describes the type of file being managed. Examples of different electronic formats include PDF, CSV, TXT, XLS, XML, etc.\n\nFor resources to be easily shared online, they must be in the same or compatible formats. Some formats are easier to share offline than others.  The chart below shows a list of popular formats with rankings from (1) worst to (3) best.\n\nPDFs are great for printing but make it nearly impossible to share their data with other systems.  \n\nCSVs are fantastic for sharing data but almost entirely unintelligible in print.  \n\n\nThe best formats for sharing news and events information is through XML formats.  Most popular website content management systems (CMS) produce XML news feeds called RSS and event feeds call iCAL. Google Calendars also produce iCAL feeds.','','','','','',''),(381,'rec5pID1W0MCr27Pi','forum','glossary','','','recV82r7ZHXB89b3T, recrTl4YzE6vWCww9','','','',''),(382,'rechLY0LYPBX8D86G','fracking','glossary','','','recZA87CVY4r3vGDF','','','',''),(383,'rec0yMvfVK4zh90xD','free open source software','glossary','','','recTA5Re6PZjUVJQC','','','',''),(384,'recX9rkkAv2GPut1a','Frontline Community','Use Case','','recEy7nfXXdLHJrX7, recS9kHmJWubiTS4c, recCIw9j0UVrrTFGf, recl1CISnR7pL4ORR, recbNQomhxuhzSppr, recSLHAxbavwLcnbE, reccNgGFTgsy2az1w','recy1j2dELpGPU0oB, recEfLIUcee7xk0ft, recpW3oeofxhjnAMj, recN2KakKtoD0JvsG, rec8RuwUezOUXuAni, recr7ojSee09Uno7n, rec2x4HcWS0fw0FIk, recqfGUpD7lXRQcH3, recHtxpB78zGgwPqj, recfAhD0tAcdvhjAI, recxBIz2Qgwr2O7qH, rec680XZ7WTeTalO2, rec86Af4whvmYfLUW, rec3G3cfzNDTsNbEH, reckVH626UkNbHGmM, recyc6f0KPrWVevL1, recqkpFofaHDHwnkE, rec5t60TAMdFYFQqw, recyEjBHi7dIGSqyI, recIadRwaqm3LK4io, recsGeRUNopSm4TCF, rec3gMO0Q3meQUzbh','recx8JohA3SXDWFrP, rec727818eSfLKkRw, recS1gsoVxfSXhtYU','','',''),(385,'reccM5SypuS2P7mol','fuel','glossary','','','recqPkDhp14BArq8P','','','',''),(386,'recyu9NYKDDxJRLCA','Fund Allocation','Challenges','A successful fund allocation process will be transparent and easy to navigate, and will enable those who recieve funds to use the allocation process to build their reputation and attract more resources going forward.\n\nAn unsuccessful process will be opaque and difficult to naviate, and groups will not want to broadcast that they recieved funds through the process.\n\nYou can also run into problems surrounding \"donor intent\" if you raise money saying it\'ll go to one thing and then spend it on something else.  For example, if you say \"all money we raise will be used for food and water\" and then you spend it on plywood and sheetrock your might be violating laws governing nonprofits in your state - and the state attorney general could strip your organization of it\'s nonprofit status.\n\nThat\'s why it\'s very important to come up with a plan easy, describe it generally on any fundraising materials that you have (website, print materials, etc) and execute your plan faithfully.  \n\nThree types of fund allocation you might want to engage in are Emergency Funds for the immediate aftermath of the storm, Project Funds for the midterm relief effort and Community-Led Budgeting for the long term recovery.\n\nAnother popular (and highly institutional) allocation strategy is the development of an Unmet Needs Fund.','recwIrBHEx2GzqFM3, recoo0FF7LYlbK8Ge, recVE2JefyvhNos32, rec21wOuVmsPSUrCx, recvhylWhiuLsgnBN, recerWLHj3n60GIuS, recofmjQDs9iDPwV8','','','','',''),(387,'recclHBYARCtgn7F2','Fund Raising','Challenges','Fundraising for disasters often begins immediately after they strike. The photos, video and narratives that emerge from the disaster compels a wide variety of people to give in a wide variety of ways.\n\ngive immediately through their cell phone or a website.  \nresearch various disaster relief groups and give to the group they find most compelling.\ngive funds that will be spent in a specific way, such as through project-based fundraising or via gift registries.\nIt\'s important to have a process for engaging with all your group\'s donors because someone who has given once to your group is many many times more likely to give again than someone who has not.\n\nConverting someone into a donor is a difficult challenge that, unfortunately, goes beyond doing amazing work that everyone wants to support.  It requires building lists of potential donors, documenting your work, inviting people to give, and convincing them that the time to give is now!','recwIrBHEx2GzqFM3, recOa4on5KBnJuoVE, recp0MapnLVbpPFBV, recI1bc212RVK7aKK, recofmjQDs9iDPwV8','','','','',''),(388,'recgxQHAtyjgSsDKW','Funder','Organization Type','','','recFE8sVVVSSyVTee, recFHw3TFUKxzKO97, recdRzY6HB5RB6HZ1, rec4lMMrTt8Lx0y2L, recEYAQexYPFllBOH, recZL8eqG5mkiG29G, rec44lFYdj5uZXjxO','','','',''),(389,'recIeEdfr0KfxM6vO','Funder','glossary','Funder â€“ groups which provide funding and other resources.','','','','','',''),(390,'rec4TRvCYRNJUOpua','Funding','data','','','','','','',''),(391,'recUuN5ZgZ0bfAN4T','Funding','Tags','','rec0ObejZLWviqo4y, recKZockwe4llzllk, recFOsjzAz1foXXtB, recVQN8ElsjBikITS, recSEvpULUnb5ASlT, recrrwRiAcXVTz7Q9, recxJi83l7ILjQ1s9, reczG1cvGoSTyrCSK, recHQPtSKq1z0TNFj, reccfMEk5bZ613ZPI, recYQUvsiCPI6cUxL','recAngoYFYkH08cYR','','','',''),(392,'recgtHhKhQbNQ0Uzw','Funding','glossary','','','recXDHXIFkopM6t7H','','','',''),(393,'recYQUvsiCPI6cUxL','Funding Local Initiatives','Tasks','Seek out funding and support opportunities for the program, the organization, and the larger ecosystem.','recgtHhKhQbNQ0Uzw, recP5VA7d5HIfa1O9','','','','',''),(394,'recTDYZokdJfDDWdV','Fundraising on your Website','Tutorials','Your website is the number main venue for your group or organization\'s fundraising.  Depending on how you set it up, your website might actually be the place where people give, or it may provide information to contextualize and support donate pages hosted on a third party fundraising web service such as IndieGogo or Kickstarter.\n','rec3NEj4ZcZ6KT0hA, recrSrttVvPPmfCBG','recZHSZypSFHafKIW, recj0ovOPuizEmxUJ, recbG1NWaWPUTYiCG, recgRCRw7pwa9XLcd','','','',''),(395,'rec6ojlkBK7hXAAdT','games','glossary','','','rec4f4lPYK3ZId23c, rec8u0DZMyJKBE5C0','','','',''),(396,'rectNQPmv6ARUdZLo','gas','glossary','','','recqPkDhp14BArq8P'