s one another, and builds power by creating opportunity for the LTRG to approach more-resoured groups (including large charities and government agencies) with a stronger voice. It is one of the best vehicles for getting residents engaged in the broader recovery effort.\n','rec3lODMUBMqDZaEk','','','','',''),(555,'rec3qMEAPvQxulexn','low-cost sensors','glossary','','','reccdat48jl16RJ2u','','','',''),(556,'recKfJcqV3PKw1XWZ','low-middle income countries','glossary','','','rectn2VAaJZtaEakR','','','',''),(557,'rectX1a1iioPat0TO','M&E','Sector','','','','','','',''),(558,'recvOm3kOKer5T5sT','machine construction systems','glossary','','','rec3hwS1GjNy3eghU','','','',''),(559,'recxTYNQwnhSC1rl6','machine learning','glossary','','','rec1o6ZzZrW4I294J, recdEInugFYktw0WM','','','',''),(560,'reccvfNa4wCo2HqTM','machines','glossary','','','rec3hwS1GjNy3eghU','','','',''),(561,'recYubQ4cMtUkKIBH','maedagua','glossary','','','rec2R4s1ASXtqj14k','','','',''),(562,'recJGE7YOFcd3GZ1r','MailingListDHN','Tags','','','','','','',''),(563,'recqrFlQS5GniLXkJ','MailingListDHN','Source','','','','','','',''),(564,'recH7IPHQ87cFj8L1','MailingListRDF','Tags','','','','','','',''),(565,'recwAUqfcLpbg9jtB','MailingListRDF','Source','','','','','','',''),(566,'recvEAD2lwzuM3x7r','Maintain documentation','Workflows','','reckNyxDnvAtVO82p, recZoqL43IBjFlcAZ','','','','Willow',''),(567,'recNweu1ptwANSAdh','Maintain inventory of incoming donations and production','Workflows','','recI3ANzRjfusxayv, recZoqL43IBjFlcAZ','','','','Willow',''),(568,'recVTTufCFkOShk8T','Maintainer of Contacts Database','Use Case','Maximize impact and engagement by enabling tailored requests to your constituents by maintaining a well-organized database of volunteers, donors, field contacts etc.','reczlQNhpfNosVLvS','recDVYNCne1Cd5L4R','','','',''),(569,'recq5l85r3cqpmDps','Maintainer of Logistics Database','Use Case','We can\'t know what we need if we don\'t know what we have. Keep data about dispatch, inventory, and needs assessment up to date so people running all over the place are doing so effectively.','recZ8ZgEq9ql8hWiL, recLFLL0fRQ1DdQ7N','','','','',''),(570,'recI7xh7DRy9F0IeT','Make contact with locals for needs assessment and checks on baseline data accuracy.','Tasks','Make contact with locals for needs assessment and checks on baseline data accuracy.','rec40sH1svojf9xpJ','','','','',''),(571,'recDtzplbDpzy5UGz','Make the information usable to decision makers and field practitioners by cleaning up the visualization, and making it printable.','Workflows','','recNg4mdUOqAOsBDs, recd6fTha4M5e2oEg','','','','Willow',''),(572,'recJwGAA0x7TOhQlE','Making Data Accessible and Interoperable','Challenges','Quite often, the most critical information that needs to be shared during disaster relief and recovery comes in the form of files such as spreadsheets and PDFs. Some of these filesshould be made available to the general public, others contain highly sensative information. that should only be accessible by specific individuals.\n\nHow do you make the right information accessible to the right people? \n\nBy using open Data Standards.\nBy using the appropriate free, and open open source software.\nBy planning your user permissions to meet your needs.','recnebUtIIFB2MmCh, recoo0FF7LYlbK8Ge, recwhC0BDxCv2XmOF, recJhvzdNTks6LNFz, rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I','rec9KuFLn69nVvWS9','','','',''),(573,'recM98NXKXaTOedJX','Manage Amazon gift registry','Workflows','','recI3ANzRjfusxayv, recZoqL43IBjFlcAZ','','','','Willow',''),(574,'reckwIXsOhNYd88py','Manage Feeds with TinyTinyRSS','Tutorials','Add Feeds\nLog into your account.  If you don\'t have an account you need to ask the system administrator to create one for you because there is no registration option.\nTo add a single feed, click the \"Actions\" drop down menu on the top right of the screen and then select \"Subscribe to Feed\", paste the Feed\'s URL and select it\'s category.\nTo add a single feed, click the \"Actions\" drop down menu on the top right of the screen and then select \"Preferences\".\nClick the \"Feeds\" tab on top left.\nIf you want to create a category for all your feed items, go to \"Categories>Add Category\".\nTo add one feed, go to \"Feeds>Subscribe to Feed\" and then paste the feed\'s URL.  You can also assign it\'s items to a category.\nTo add multiple feeds, go to \"Feed>Batch Subscribe\".  Select the category and then paste the URLs of all the feeds into the large field, with one feed on each line and press \"Subscribe\".\nNow you can either wait for the feeds to automatically populate or exit the \"Preferences\" area and double click on the feed names on the left to get them to manually populate. \nManage Folders/Categories\nTo create folders you\'re actually creating \"Categories\":\nGo to to right \"Actions\" > \"Preference\"\nClick on the \"Feeds\" tab > \"Categories\" > \"Add Category\"\nYou\'ll see that a folder appears in the Feeds list.  You can drag the folder/category into other folders/categories to create hierarchical structure.\nAdd Feeds to Categories\nDouble click on the feed and then select the appropriate category in the dialog box.\n\nYou can drag and drop feeds into the appropraite folders as well.','recYyj1U8W8quyzhz, recQZtGMy5sgFvIRi','recaUFitVcT2hhzYo, recn2Fe6mUozKtlNU','','','',''),(575,'recBaqkVB92VT66oX','Manage Google Folder Permissions','Tutorials','You can share a Google Folder (collaborative documents) with everyone in a Google Group simply by using the Google Groupâ€™s email address.  This allows you to manage access to your Google Folder by managing access to your Google Group.\n','recFmTEL3UuvxzYJz','recUiHoYSXjwhqwsl','','','',''),(576,'rec67LQ7smpAw91Gt','Management','Use Case','','recIMA1ty9QITjcq5, recSEvpULUnb5ASlT','recfKzhFLiSczod2U, recAngoYFYkH08cYR','','','',''),(577,'recVQN8ElsjBikITS','Managers at district water agency allocating resources and time of district water engineers','Workflows','','recgtHhKhQbNQ0Uzw, rec1C1xZ9gNa3wVb7','','','','Willow',''),(578,'reckRvwsJ4rLE7Ul8','Managing Human Services Resources','Challenges','During and after a disaster, relief providers need good information about where to refer victims for \"human services\" assistance such as homeless shelters, mental health counselling, food pantries, insurance advice and so much more. Unlike local business information, which was made readily available via the internet over a decade ago, â€œhuman serviceâ€ information is much more difficult to find - even if you\'re a nonprofit organizastion.  This is especially true in New York City, which doesn\'t have a nonprofit-run 211 system like most other places in the USA.\n\nThis creates a problem for relief providers who want to ensure victims get high quality information and can access critical servicesâ€”and also makes it difficult for relief communites to create their own resource directories.','recnebUtIIFB2MmCh, recoo0FF7LYlbK8Ge, recOa4on5KBnJuoVE, recdcveRb1arT5kZU, rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I','','','','',''),(579,'recEtIwLKglEs5fjQ','Managing Inquiries','Challenges','If a relief group or network has a public phone number or email address, itâ€™s likely that it will be flooded with inquiries from a wide variety of people, including volunteers who want to help out, high-dollar donors that want to give money, people who need emergency assistance, people who have general questions, the press/media and more. Often the person who receives a request is not the same person who can fulfill it, so people pass requests from one to another, and hope that the right person receives the information and can act upon it. Without a way to track these requests, all people can do is cross their fingers and trust in the universe to take care of thingsâ€”usually leading to many new problems.','recOa4on5KBnJuoVE, recdcveRb1arT5kZU, rechRM6Mk5F2Mw0FV, rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I, recFN89wM7ldOSmK8','','','','',''),(580,'recjjyxfA2BlPRyve','Managing Needs Information','Challenges','For many groups, the top priority immediately after a disaster takes place is fulfilling the needs of individuals and groups affected by the event.  This requires identifying what the needs are, acquring the resources needed to meet those needs, deploying those resources and determining whether of not a need is fulfilled so the next set of needs can be tackled.\n\nThere are many channels through which needs information can flow, and having a way to collect and action information from each of those channels will ensure you\'re getting the most and best information possible.\n\nChannels include:\nSocial Media\nPhone Calls\nSMS\nSpreadsheets\nOnline Forms\nOffline Forms\nCanvassing','recoo0FF7LYlbK8Ge, recW4gfJIWhRniBIg, rec8l7igQjaQvnj9I, recYMbCtiPLmAtyHW, recFN89wM7ldOSmK8, rechRM6Mk5F2Mw0FV','','','','',''),(581,'recc2wjkByadUJo2K','Managing Volunteers','Challenges','Disaster relief requires a wide range of people and skillsâ€”from accountants to carpenterss and designers to truck drivers. How can you attract the volunteers the relief effort needs, how can you help them be useful to the effort, and how can you facilitate their longer-term commitment?','rec1N4BMHzDqAzNnp, recJnh92lheoUrwA9, rec9nelsOzk2AwHnk','rec4rTTDHxNrTLzMS','','','',''),(582,'rece4fq1U0CiuGyuY','map','glossary','','','recBkUHCCazoLIiiS, recn8bIuYnvbUufkq','','','',''),(583,'recoNtpfCtb1kuLZ9','map included','glossary','','','recPi7di0oYsR7yGM','','','',''),(584,'recpA7yg8NYxJ6jhs','map layers','glossary','','','recTQpuCXRLTDEF1X','','','',''),(585,'recfxxooUSe9kdOPu','Map Making with CiviCRM','Tutorials','Mapping Contacts in CiviCRM:\nGo to Contacts > Manage Groups\nSelect the Group that contains contacts you want to map.  This could be a regular group or smart group that contacts are automatically placed into once they fill out a specific form.\nClick the check boxes next to the groups you want to see placed onto a map\nActivate the \"actions\" drop down menu and select \"map contacts\"\nClick \"Go\" and you should get a map\nNote: for Geo codding to work well, you must enable the Cron for it under Administer> System Settings > Scheduled Jobs (referenced here: http://book.civicrm.org/user/current/initial-set-up/scheduled-jobs/). You\'ll need to enable Geocode and Parse Addresses to update daily. What this does it parses the latitude & longitude to be able to display on a map. There are limitations from Google on how many contacts can be updated daily, so if there are already a lot of contacts it may take sometime to update, otherwise it will just update the contacts that don\'t have the lat & long details for mapping.','recmFBM3jsCvmbqtC, recdZk6CZiTywlVag','recZHSZypSFHafKIW','','','',''),(586,'recy4fsU9qsPfeiuF','Map Making with Google Fusion Tables','Tutorials','Google Fusion Tables is a really handy tool for turning spreadsheets into interactive maps.  Here\'s how:\n\n\n\nCreate a Map\nLog into Google via your gmail.com email address or use your own email address that associated with a Google Account.  If you\'re using an email address powered by Google Apps, you will not be able to create a map with it.  I don\'t know why.  If that\'s the case, use/create and log in with an @gmail.com address.\nGo to \"Drive\" on the black, top nav bar.\nCreate a Google Spreadsheet file.  If you already have a spreadsheet with location informtaion in .csv format, click on the little red \"Upload\" button next to the \"Create\" button.  A message will appear when the file starts uploading.  In that message there is a small box that says \"Convert this to the appropriate Google format\".  Make sure it\'s checked.  It usually is by default.  If you want to create a new spreadsheet, go to \"Create\"  and click \"Spreadsheet\".\nAdd your data into the Google Spreadsheet.  Make sure your location information is either a (postal style) address with all information in a single column or latitutde and longitude numbers in two columns.  Also make sure your first row contains headers.  There headers will become the labels for the fields that appear in your map.\nConvert your Spreadsheet into a Fusion Table by back to your drive.google.com homepage, going to \"Create\" on the top left, and then selecting \"Fusion Table\".  If \"Fusion Table\" isn\'t an option, click \"Connect More Apps\", search for \"Fusion Tables\" and click \"+Connect\".  Go through the very brief instalation process.  Then repeat the instruction in the first sentence.\nThe first screen says \"Import new table\".  Select the second option: \"Google Spreadsheet\".  It will give you a screen with all the Spreadsheets in your Google Drive.  Find the one you want to map and select it.\nIt will ask you the location of your column names.  Hopefully your answer is 1 so you can click \"Next\".\nAttribution is very important.  Do you want people to have the ability to copy/export the data?  Who should the data be attributed to?  Answer these questions and click \"Finish\".\nCongratulations, now you have a fusion table!  Go to the little red \"plus\" icon next to \"Cards 1\", click it and select \"Add Map\".  If you\'re accidently signed in with a Google Apps email account, you will not be able to create an account.  Share the Fusion Table with an @gmail.com account, log into that account and redo this step.\nWhen you create a map it\'ll automatically guess which column has the location information and try to geocode it.  Click \"next\" until it\'s done.  If it selected the wrong column, which it often does, click on the little arrow next to \"Map 1\", go to \"select location\" and click the appropriate column option.  If the appropriate column option doesn\'t exist there have no fear!  Go to \"Edit\" > \"Change Columns\", select the column with the location information, go to \"Type\" and select \"Location\" from the drop down menu.  Then repeat this step.\nNow you should have a map with points on it.  If you click on a point you\'ll get all the information in the row of that location.  Pat yourself on the back - you did it.  You can do a lot of customization. Google explains how.  This guide will continue with information about how to embed this map into a website.\n\nEmbed a Map\nGo to your Google Fusion Table of choice, .\nClick \"Change Visibility\", make it \"Public on the Web\" and click \"Done\".\nAgain: Click the little arrow on your map tab and then click \"Publish\".  Change the width and height to suite your needs.  Copy the HTML embed code and paste it onto your website.  If you don\'t know how to embed HTML on your website, Website+Embed HTML.','recmFBM3jsCvmbqtC, rec31B4uFy6AxksQH','recXT2dYnUA3l5mmE','','','',''),(587,'reco8i5EG8Vp08KuC','Mapping','Tool Type','','recnPgj79mPJq4krX','rec8RuwUezOUXuAni, recxnxMcGsMhKbKDv, rec1alzp4ErFWvQj7, recBRw30Cs2zjBsle, rechqDtrIw82FHBt2','','','','map'),(588,'recO3liHpQRhXNBQ7','Mapping','Tags','','recOnO3n3CM0xFhOJ, recK7yBQx4jabhZY8','rechqDtrIw82FHBt2, rechW3yhHm1StYFp6, recoWn7ptWrjJqcCy, recTq79NCBLZTsJv2, recLw4ni1UNGRsAJk, reckVH626UkNbHGmM, recCygOOk3MAPv3hm, rec2U2HHGDuYjqiYt, recxKncZIoA7qMtWb','rec8hzr7SfaNeygUL, recYb252qdDmwKmBj','','',''),(589,'rec9HAiVGoSzKqOVh','Mapping','glossary','','','recbvAFbWHqbjk2kx, reccvc4B6DBV9GqDW, rec8VYBCc1YA1Nt4P, recG4tXRjK5rYk1ZZ, recWP4WwLg6t9dBEo, recxnxMcGsMhKbKDv, recXl9ndVRRiDwmKk, recTQzSm7d1e6hujp, recIhGfpKtz2rndqf, recr7ojSee09Uno7n, rec0n9Hm6ncUXW6dp','','','',''),(590,'recmFBM3jsCvmbqtC','Mapping','Toolboxes','Putting data onto a map is one of the easiest ways to make it understandable and actionable.','recy4fsU9qsPfeiuF, recfxxooUSe9kdOPu, recmpIjtnQjN70nAK, recZjjj5j5FcsxfAU, recx0OssEEfyX8JBj','','','','',''),(591,'reci2tPxt6BTJ6Mib','mapping','glossary','','','recEfLIUcee7xk0ft, recMspjDoOBLESkb8, recZA87CVY4r3vGDF, reccEGzVMPWzVh0JP, reclmAm6bGKBDD6wm, recBRw30Cs2zjBsle, rec8RuwUezOUXuAni, recPxlJDZ9xvTIQzX, rec4xRnv7vjttslFc','','','',''),(592,'reckj2auhsnpW9D0U','mapping data','glossary','','','recoxM9POOYtkW78t','','','',''),(593,'recKa2T3QkUs4QSad','