ort available','glossary','','','recTA5Re6PZjUVJQC','','','',''),(737,'recublCaKXDQdTDls','Programmes','Organization Type','','','recYUukrnFj20Sl5e, recBdxRC7KHyHP2NJ','','','',''),(738,'recQQYJxe7GmxyscD','Project Funding Templates','Tutorials','','recvhylWhiuLsgnBN, recNmMk2QPPkX908b','recMF0w6LFawMmuLx','','','',''),(739,'recvhylWhiuLsgnBN','Project Funds','Toolboxes','Once the initial phase of the disaster is over, funding should transition away from emergency funds and into project-based funding. At this point, people will have the time and situational awareness necessary to develop more strategic project proposals that address the need of affected communities.  \n\nThese needs vary. A few examples of successful projects that came out of grassroots responses to Superstorm Sandy include: purchasing tools and materials for muckouts and rebuilding work, restoring workspaces in affected areas, purchasing vehicles for relief workers, designing wayfinding graphics for affected communities and funding media and documentation tools.\n','recQQYJxe7GmxyscD, recyu9NYKDDxJRLCA','','','','',''),(740,'recIMA1ty9QITjcq5','Project Management','data','Fulfill responsibilities and make use of opportunities by viewing the tasks of a project, their status, and who is responsible for delivery.','recpMPHSM9vY43lnn','','','','',''),(741,'rechWDUBsFFMlGj2D','project management','glossary','overview and planning of project timeline and implementation','recIMA1ty9QITjcq5, rec5s6dhq2DaMOwud, recHjAGJjAQxL0naU','recdEInugFYktw0WM','','','',''),(742,'recerWLHj3n60GIuS','Project Spokescouncil','Toolboxes','A Project Spokescouncil can be a useful meeting structure for coordination. It brings different projects in together for regular networking and sharing, leading to the synergy that only face-to-face contact allows.\n\n\n\nIt\'s also a useful structure for determining which groups can access certain scarce resources like project funds and vehicles. \n','recOwT1pHRQhQRVuE, rec478jcu2UFRzEUL, recyu9NYKDDxJRLCA, recZjjj5j5FcsxfAU','','','','',''),(743,'reczKD3zp4j63JIEv','promote','Skills','','','','','','',''),(744,'rec0LyYH8YOarbfSs','promote','Skills','','','','','','',''),(745,'recH7o5FfMxVzZ7Hf','promotes computer and technology','glossary','','','recWiEy3n8ld1QOMt','','','',''),(746,'reclpdzG4gwRFdpf4','Protected Data Sharing','Toolboxes','The blockchain can overcome these barriers to data sharing\nby providing an information marketplace that is publicly\naccessible to all users while ensuring information security.\nIn particular, the blockchain lends itself well to being â€œa universal, permanent, searchable, irrevocable public records repository.â€ A combination of time-stamped and digitally\nverified information hosted on an accessible ledger could\nplay an important role in reducing costs and increasing transparency\nwith humanitarian data. Projects such as Ascribe.ioâ€™s\nBigChainDB are making use of this concept to build blockchain-enabled\ndatabases.24\nDue to the blockchainâ€™s distributed nature, it is possible to\nhave different humanitarian agencies being able to collect\nand share data on the same network. By reducing cost for\nprotected data while enabling data sharing between entities,\nthis allows for the creation of information marketplaces in the\nhumanitarian sector. Companies such as Stampery already\nuse the technology to notarize information and ensure proof\nof ownership by providing time-stamped data in an unalterable\nstate.\nAdditionally, the use of blockchain will help ensure greater\ndata security while increasing coordination and transparency.\nThe use of digital signatures increases privacy by protecting\nthe person posting the data. Moreover, compartments within\nthe blockchain protect data by only allowing those with the\nnecessary permissions to access it. Then, through the digital\nsignatures, it is possible to trace owners of different data\ncompartments in the blockchain for accountability. A blockchain-based\ni